 10  
 11  Throughout the `linear_map` section implicit `{}` brackets are often used instead of type class `[]` brackets.
 12  This is done when the instances can be inferred because they are implicit arguments to the type `linear_map`.
 13  When they can be inferred from the type it is faster to use this method than to use type class inference
 14  
 15  -/

 30  /-- A semimodule is a generalization of vector spaces to a scalar semiring.
 31    It consists of a scalar semiring `α` and an additive monoid of "vectors" `β`,
 32    connected by a "scalar multiplication" operation `r • x : β`
 33    (where `r : α` and `x : β`) with some natural associativity and
 34    distributivity axioms similar to those on a ring. -/

374  library_note "vector space definition"
375  "Vector spaces are defined as an `abbreviation` for modules,
376  if the base ring is a field.
377  (A previous definition made `vector_space` a structure
378  defined to be `module`.)
379  This has as advantage that vector spaces are completely transparant
380  for type class inference, which means that all instances for modules
381  are immediately picked up for vector spaces as well.
382  A cosmetic disadvantage is that one can not extend vector spaces an sich,
383  in definitions such as `normed_space`.
384  The solution is to extend `module` instead."
385  
386  /-- A vector space is the same as a module, except the scalar ring is actually
387    a field. (This adds commutativity of the multiplication and existence of inverses.)
388    This is the traditional generalization of spaces like `ℝ^n`, which have a natural
389    addition operation and a way to multiply them by real numbers, but no multiplication
390    operation between vectors. -/
391  abbreviation vector_space (α : Type u) (β : Type v) [discrete_field α] [add_comm_group β] :=
id                                                        └────────────┘ ┴   └────────────┘ ┴
src                                                       └────────────┘     └────────────┘
typ                                                       └────────────┘ ┴   └────────────┘ ┴

id   └────┘ ┴ ┴
src  └────┘
typ  └────┘ ┴ ┴
doc  └────┘
